description:
## Summary
Create custom Markdoc tag definitions and corresponding React components to replace all GitBook-proprietary syntax used in the documentation. These tags will be used when converting content files in later epics.

## Context
This project is a Next.js + Markdoc documentation site in the `documentation/` directory. The previous documentation was built with GitBook, which uses proprietary template tags. We need Markdoc equivalents.

The project uses `@markdoc/next.js` which automatically discovers tag definitions in `markdoc/tags/` and makes them available in `.md` files.

### GitBook syntax that needs Markdoc replacements:

1. **Columns layout** -- Used in `README.md` (2 column groups):
```
{% columns %}
{% column %}
Content here
{% endcolumn %}
{% column %}
More content
{% endcolumn %}
{% endcolumns %}
```

2. **Hint/callout boxes** -- Used in `deep-dive-the-work-scope.md` (1 instance):
```
{% hint style="info" %}
This is an informational callout.
{% endhint %}
```

3. **Figure/image with caption** -- Used in `README.md` (2 instances) and `introduction-to-impact-claims.md` (1 instance):
```html
<figure><img src=".gitbook/assets/image.png" alt=""><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
```

### How Markdoc tags work with @markdoc/next.js:

1. Tag definitions go in `markdoc/tags/*.markdoc.js` -- these define the tag name, allowed attributes, and which React component to render
2. React components go in `components/` -- these render the actual HTML
3. `@markdoc/next.js` auto-discovers tag files in `markdoc/tags/` and wires them up
4. Components are registered in `pages/_app.js` via a components mapping passed to the renderer

## What You Need to Create

### 1. Callout Tag

**Tag definition** -- `markdoc/tags/callout.markdoc.js`:
```js
export const callout = {
  render: 'Callout',
  children: ['paragraph', 'tag', 'list'],
  attributes: {
    type: {
      type: String,
      default: 'info',
      matches: ['info', 'warning', 'danger', 'success'],
      errorLevel: 'critical'
    },
    title: {
      type: String
    }
  }
};
```

**React component** -- `components/Callout.js`:

Visual design (Stripe-inspired):
- Container with a 4px left border in accent color
- Light tinted background matching the type
- Border-radius: 6px on the right side (or all corners)
- Padding: 16px
- Body text in regular weight, dark gray
- If title provided, render it bold above the body

Color mapping by type:
- `info`: blue left border (#0570de), very light blue background (#f0f7ff)
- `warning`: orange left border (#c84801), very light orange background (#fef9f0)
- `danger`: red left border (#df1b41), very light red background (#fef0f4)
- `success`: green left border (#228403), very light green background (#f0fef0)

The component should accept `type`, `title`, and `children` props.

**Markdoc usage** (what content authors will write):
```
{% callout type="info" %}
This is an informational callout.
{% /callout %}
```

### 2. Columns / Column Tags

**Tag definitions** -- `markdoc/tags/columns.markdoc.js`:
```js
export const columns = {
  render: 'Columns',
  children: ['tag'],
  attributes: {
    gap: {
      type: String,
      default: '24px'
    }
  }
};
```

`markdoc/tags/column.markdoc.js`:
```js
export const column = {
  render: 'Column',
  children: ['paragraph', 'tag', 'list', 'heading', 'image', 'fence'],
};
```

**React components**:

`components/Columns.js`:
- CSS flexbox container: `display: flex; gap: 24px;`
- On mobile (< 768px): `flex-direction: column` (stack vertically)
- On desktop: `flex-direction: row` (side by side)

`components/Column.js`:
- `flex: 1` (equal width columns)
- Renders children directly

**Markdoc usage**:
```
{% columns %}
{% column %}
Left content
{% /column %}
{% column %}
Right content
{% /column %}
{% /columns %}
```

### 3. Figure Tag

**Tag definition** -- `markdoc/tags/figure.markdoc.js`:
```js
export const figure = {
  render: 'Figure',
  selfClosing: true,
  attributes: {
    src: { type: String, required: true },
    alt: { type: String, default: '' },
    caption: { type: String }
  }
};
```

**React component** -- `components/Figure.js`:

Visual design:
- Centered container (`text-align: center; margin: 24px 0`)
- Image with `max-width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: 6px`
- Caption (if provided) rendered below in small text (13px), secondary gray color (#687385), margin-top: 8px

**Markdoc usage**:
```
{% figure src="/images/hypercert-erd.png" alt="Hypercert ERD" caption="Entity relationship diagram" /%}
```

### 4. Export all tags -- `markdoc/tags/index.js`:
```js
export { callout } from './callout.markdoc';
export { columns } from './columns.markdoc';
export { column } from './column.markdoc';
export { figure } from './figure.markdoc';
```

### 5. Register components in `pages/_app.js`:
Update the existing `_app.js` to pass components:
```jsx
import '../styles/globals.css';
import { Callout } from '../components/Callout';
import { Columns } from '../components/Columns';
import { Column } from '../components/Column';
import { Figure } from '../components/Figure';

const components = {
  Callout,
  Columns,
  Column,
  Figure,
};

export default function App({ Component, pageProps }) {
  return <Component {...pageProps} components={components} />;
}
```

Note: With `@markdoc/next.js`, components can also be passed via the Markdoc config. Check the @markdoc/next.js docs if the above pattern doesn't wire up correctly -- the alternative is to use a `markdoc/config.js` file.

### 6. Verify
Create a test page `pages/test-tags.md` with all three tags to verify they render:
```markdown
---
title: Tag Test
---

# Tag Test

{% callout type="info" %}
This is an info callout.
{% /callout %}

{% callout type="warning" title="Warning" %}
This is a warning.
{% /callout %}

{% columns %}
{% column %}
**Left column** with some content.
{% /column %}
{% column %}
**Right column** with some content.
{% /column %}
{% /columns %}

{% figure src="/images/hypercert-erd.png" alt="Test image" caption="A test caption" /%}
```

Run `npm run dev` and verify all tags render correctly. Delete the test page after verification.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `markdoc/tags/callout.markdoc.js` exists with type attribute (info, warning, danger, success)
- `components/Callout.js` renders a styled callout box with 4px colored left border and tinted background
- `markdoc/tags/columns.markdoc.js` and `markdoc/tags/column.markdoc.js` exist
- `components/Columns.js` renders a CSS flexbox multi-column layout that stacks on mobile
- `components/Column.js` renders individual column content with flex: 1
- `markdoc/tags/figure.markdoc.js` exists as a self-closing tag with src, alt, caption attributes
- `components/Figure.js` renders a centered image with optional gray caption text
- `markdoc/tags/index.js` exports all tags
- Components are registered in `pages/_app.js` so Markdoc can render them
- All tags render correctly when used in .md files via `npm run dev`

## Summary
Create the complete CSS styling for the documentation site following a design language inspired by Stripe's documentation (docs.stripe.com). The goal is a clean, professional, content-focused documentation site that prioritizes readability and quiet confidence.

## Context
This project is a Next.js + Markdoc documentation site in the `documentation/` directory. By the time this epic runs:
- Epic 1 has scaffolded the project with a minimal `styles/globals.css`
- Epic 2 has created React components: Callout, Columns, Column, Figure
- Epic 4 has created Layout, Sidebar, TableOfContents components

All these components need polished CSS. The styles go in `styles/globals.css` (or can be split into CSS modules if preferred).

## Design Principles

The Stripe documentation design language follows these core principles:
1. **Content is the interface** -- every visual decision makes content more scannable, never decorates
2. **Mostly monochrome, with surgical color** -- the page is 95% grayscale; color appears only for links, callout indicators, and status badges
3. **Generous but purposeful whitespace** -- everything breathes, nothing floats
4. **Border, not shadow, for structure** -- 1px light gray borders define regions, not heavy shadows
5. **Developer-first** -- code blocks are first-class citizens, typography is optimized for technical content

## Typography

### Font stacks
```css
--font-sans: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol';
--font-mono: 'Source Code Pro', Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
```
Use the system font stack. It loads instantly, feels native on every OS, and is what Stripe uses.

### Font weights
- Regular: 400 (body text, descriptions)
- Semibold: 600 (section headers, emphasis, sidebar labels)
- Bold: 700 (page titles, H1)

### Type scale
| Element | Size | Weight | Color | Line Height |
|---------|------|--------|-------|-------------|
| H1 | 32px | 700 | #21252c (near-black) | 1.25 |
| H2 | 24px | 700 | #353a44 (dark charcoal) | 1.3 |
| H3 | 20px | 600 | #353a44 | 1.4 |
| H4 | 16px | 600 | #353a44 | 1.5 |
| Body | 16px | 400 | #414552 (dark gray) | 1.65 |
| Small/Caption | 13px | 400 | #687385 (medium gray) | 1.5 |
| Code (inline) | 14px | 400 | #414552 | inherit |
| Code (block) | 14px | 400 | #414552 | 1.55 |

### Anti-aliasing
```css
body {
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
}
```

## Color Palette

### Neutrals (the workhorse -- 95% of the page)
| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| --color-bg | #ffffff | Page background, content area |
| --color-bg-subtle | #f6f8fa | Code block backgrounds, sidebar hover, cards |
| --color-border | #ebeef1 | Section dividers, sidebar border, card borders |
| --color-border-strong | #d8dee4 | Table header bottom border, input borders |
| --color-text-secondary | #687385 | Descriptions, metadata, TOC items, captions |
| --color-text-primary | #414552 | Body text |
| --color-text-heading | #353a44 | Headings (H2-H4) |
| --color-text-title | #21252c | H1 page titles |

### Accent colors (used sparingly -- only for interactive elements and semantic indicators)
| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| --color-link | #0570de | Hyperlinks, interactive text |
| --color-link-hover | #0055bc | Link hover state (slightly darker) |
| --color-info | #0570de | Info callout border |
| --color-info-bg | #f0f7ff | Info callout background |
| --color-warning | #c84801 | Warning callout border |
| --color-warning-bg | #fef9f0 | Warning callout background |
| --color-danger | #df1b41 | Danger callout border |
| --color-danger-bg | #fef0f4 | Danger callout background |
| --color-success | #228403 | Success callout border |
| --color-success-bg | #f0fef0 | Success callout background |

### Focus ring
```css
--focus-ring: 0 0 0 4px rgba(5, 112, 222, 0.36);
```

## Spacing System

Use an 8px base grid. All spacing should be multiples of 8 (with 4px for tight spaces):
```css
--space-1: 4px;
--space-2: 8px;
--space-3: 12px;
--space-4: 16px;
--space-5: 20px;
--space-6: 24px;
--space-8: 32px;
--space-10: 40px;
--space-12: 48px;
--space-16: 64px;
```

### Application:
- Between paragraphs: 16px
- Between heading and its first paragraph: 8-12px (tight coupling)
- Before a new H2 section: 48px (creates visible section breaks)
- Sidebar item vertical spacing: 4-6px between items, 20-24px between section groups
- Content area horizontal padding: 32px on each side
- Content area top padding: 32px below header

## Component Styles

### Layout
```
Header: height 56px, white background, bottom border 1px solid #ebeef1
Sidebar: width 240px, fixed/sticky, right border 1px solid #ebeef1, padding 16px
Content: max-width 720px, centered, padding 32px
Right TOC: width 200px, sticky top, padding-left 24px
```

### Sidebar
- Section headers: 12px, font-weight 600, color #687385, text-transform uppercase, letter-spacing 0.05em, margin-bottom 8px
- Nav items: 14px, color #414552, padding 6px 12px, border-radius 6px
- Active nav item: font-weight 600, background-color #f6f8fa, color #21252c
- Hover nav item: background-color #f6f8fa
- Nested items: padding-left +16px

### Table of Contents (right side)
- Title "On this page": 12px, font-weight 600, color #687385, uppercase
- Items: 13px, color #687385, padding 4px 0
- Active item: color #0570de (link blue)
- Left border indicator: 2px solid #0570de on active item (optional)

### Callout boxes (from Epic 2 components)
```css
.callout {
  border-left: 4px solid var(--callout-color);
  background: var(--callout-bg);
  border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
  padding: 16px;
  margin: 16px 0;
}
.callout-title {
  font-weight: 600;
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}
```

### Columns layout (from Epic 2 components)
```css
.columns {
  display: flex;
  gap: 24px;
  margin: 16px 0;
}
.column {
  flex: 1;
  min-width: 0;
}
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .columns { flex-direction: column; }
}
```

### Figure (from Epic 2 components)
```css
.figure {
  text-align: center;
  margin: 24px 0;
}
.figure img {
  max-width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  border-radius: 6px;
}
.figure-caption {
  font-size: 13px;
  color: #687385;
  margin-top: 8px;
}
```

### Tables
Stripe uses clean, borderless tables with only a header bottom border:
```css
table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  margin: 16px 0;
  font-size: 14px;
}
th {
  text-align: left;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: #353a44;
  padding: 8px 12px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #d8dee4;
}
td {
  padding: 8px 12px;
  color: #414552;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #ebeef1;
}
tr:last-child td {
  border-bottom: none;
}
```
No zebra striping. No outer borders. Clean and minimal.

### Code blocks
```css
pre {
  background: #f6f8fa;
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 16px;
  overflow-x: auto;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 14px;
  line-height: 1.55;
  margin: 16px 0;
  color: #414552;
}
```
Optionally install `prism-react-renderer` for syntax highlighting. The current docs only have 2 JSON code blocks, but the SDK docs will grow. If adding syntax highlighting, use a light theme that matches the neutral palette.

### Inline code
```css
code {
  background: #f6f8fa;
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 2px 6px;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 0.875em; /* slightly smaller than surrounding text */
}
/* Don't style code inside pre blocks */
pre code {
  background: none;
  border-radius: 0;
  padding: 0;
  font-size: inherit;
}
```

### Links
```css
a {
  color: #0570de;
  text-decoration: none;
}
a:hover {
  color: #0055bc;
  text-decoration: underline;
}
```

### Headings
```css
h1 { font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; color: #21252c; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 16px; line-height: 1.25; }
h2 { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; color: #353a44; margin-top: 48px; margin-bottom: 12px; line-height: 1.3; }
h3 { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; color: #353a44; margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 8px; line-height: 1.4; }
h4 { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; color: #353a44; margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 8px; line-height: 1.5; }
```

Note: `h2` has 48px top margin to create strong visual section breaks (the largest gaps on the page). This is a key Stripe pattern.

### Pagination (prev/next)
```css
.pagination {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  margin-top: 48px;
  padding-top: 24px;
  border-top: 1px solid #ebeef1;
}
.pagination a {
  color: #0570de;
  font-weight: 500;
}
```

### Lists
```css
ul, ol {
  padding-left: 24px;
  margin: 12px 0;
}
li {
  margin: 6px 0;
  line-height: 1.65;
}
li > p { margin: 0; }
```

### Blockquotes
```css
blockquote {
  border-left: 4px solid #ebeef1;
  padding: 0 16px;
  margin: 16px 0;
  color: #687385;
}
```

### Horizontal rules
```css
hr {
  border: none;
  border-top: 1px solid #ebeef1;
  margin: 32px 0;
}
```

## Responsive Breakpoints
```css
/* Mobile: < 768px - sidebar and TOC hidden, content full width */
/* Tablet: 768px - 1040px - sidebar visible, TOC hidden */
/* Desktop: > 1040px - full three-column layout */
```

On mobile:
- Sidebar hidden behind hamburger menu
- Right TOC hidden entirely
- Content goes full-width with 16px horizontal padding
- Tables get `overflow-x: auto` wrapper

## Shadow System
Shadows are used very sparingly -- almost never on the docs site:
- Most elements: no shadow (flat)
- Card hover: `0px 2px 5px rgba(48, 49, 61, 0.08)` (barely perceptible)
- Dropdown/overlay: `0px 5px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12), 0px 15px 35px rgba(48, 49, 61, 0.08)`

## Border Radius
- Inline code: 4px
- Code blocks, callouts, cards: 6px
- Buttons, tags, pills: 6px or rounded (9999em for pill shape)

## Acceptance Criteria
- All CSS is in `styles/globals.css` (or organized into CSS modules)
- CSS custom properties are defined for colors, fonts, and spacing
- System font stack is used (no custom font downloads)
- Anti-aliased text rendering is enabled
- All headings (H1-H4) follow the type scale with proper size, weight, color, and spacing
- Body text is 16px, dark gray (#414552), line-height 1.65
- Links are blue (#0570de), darken on hover, no underline by default
- Tables are clean: no outer borders, header has bottom border only, proper padding
- Code blocks have light gray background, rounded corners, monospace font
- Inline code has subtle gray background pill
- Callout boxes have colored left border and tinted background per type
- Columns stack on mobile, flex row on desktop
- Layout uses three columns on desktop (sidebar 240px, content ~720px, TOC ~200px)
- Sidebar has 1px right border, section headers in uppercase small text
- Active nav item has bold text and subtle background
- Right TOC has scroll spy highlighting in blue
- Responsive: sidebar/TOC collapse below 768px/1040px breakpoints
- Pagination has top border separator and blue link text
- The overall feel is clean, white, professional, content-focused -- no decorative elements, no gradients, no heavy shadows
- The page looks like it could belong to the same family as docs.stripe.com
